  "prompt": "What should I do with someone who talks behind my back and is a fake friend?",
  "response": "Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. Confront them directly\n- Calmly discuss the issue\n- Express how their behavior makes you feel\n- Give them a chance to explain themselves\n\n2. Distance yourself\n- Reduce contact and interaction\n- Limit their access to personal information\n- Focus on genuine, supportive friendships\n\n3. Set clear boundaries\n- Be clear about what behavior is unacceptable\n- Don't engage in drama or gossip\n- Maintain your integrity\n\n4. Prioritize your mental health\n- Don't let their actions affect your self-worth\n- Surround yourself with positive people\n- Consider talking to trusted friends or family\n\n5. If the situation is severe\n- Cut off the friendship completely\n- Block them on social media if necessary\n- Avoid mutual confrontations that could escalate\n\n6. Learn from the experience\n- Reflect on the friendship\n- Recognize red flags in future relationships\n- Develop stronger judgment about people's character\n\nRemember, true friends support and respect you. You deserve relationships built on trust and mutual respect.\n\nWould you like to discuss this situation in more detail?",
